ch.codebulb.lambdaomega

Class V2<X,Y>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions.OmegaObject
      • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.V2<X,Y>
  • Type Parameters:
    X - the type of the 1st element
    Y - the type of the 2nd element
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    I<Integer,Object>, ReadonlyIndexedI<Integer,Object>

    public class V2<X,Y>
extends OmegaObject
implements ReadonlyIndexedI<Integer,Object>
    The "V2" stands for "2d vector". This is an implementation of a 2-dimensional vector = a 2-ary tuple.

    The constructor of this class is not visible; use the convenience v(Object, Object) method to create a new instance of this class. It's best practice to statically import this function in client code.
